Snow and ice: 24 districts on orange alert
Snowfall continues to cause traffic difficulties, especially on the secondary network in Brittany, and may affect various economic activities.
Twenty-four departments are currently on orange alert due to the risk of snowfall and ice formation.
Eure, Eure-et-Loir, Deux-Sèvres and Vienne have joined the 20 departments already on orange alert, 18 from Wednesday to noon and two, the Dordogne and Gironde, joined the group overnight.
